# Contributing to Awesome Cybersecurity 🔐

Thanks for helping improve this list.

## 📌 Guidelines

- Only high-quality, maintained resources
- No duplicates
- Prefer official docs or well-known repos
- Add a short description (1 line max)
- Keep categories consistent

## 🧱 Format

- [Project Name](URL) – Short description

## 🚫 Not Allowed

- Dead links
- Spam / self-promotion without value
- Low-quality or outdated tools

## ✅ Pull Request Checklist

- [ ] Link works
- [ ] Fits correct category
- [ ] No duplicates
- [ ] Description added

## 🛠️ Local Check

Run:

```bash
gem install awesome_bot
awesome_bot README.md